On July 24, 2011, the President declared a national emergency regarding transnational criminal organizations due to their threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. On March 15, 2019, additional measures were taken to address this national emergency. The President has now decided to continue the national emergency for another year, citing the ongoing threat posed by these criminal organizations. This decision is made under the National Emergencies Act and will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.